{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012ptNjcduDn17UtwdKMbHh5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NAG6d5VfPcL2oWtEZiFf6s","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'EOF'\n==========================================================\nRAY CLUSTER CONFIGURATION AUDIT REPORT\nNamespace : ray\nAudit Date: 2026-06-14\nAuditor   : KARMA read-only audit (no cluster changes made)\n==========================================================\n\n--- 1. WORKER REPLICA COUNT ---\nDeployment : ray-worker\nSpec replicas (desired) : 1\nReady replicas (actual)  : 1\nStatus                   : Available / Progressing\n\nDeviation: Worker count is at the minimum (1 replica). No horizontal\nscale-up has been applied. Workloads requiring parallelism may be\nconstrained; review and increase replicas before the next change window\nif higher throughput is needed.\n\n--- 2. IMAGE VERSIONS ---\nray-head   : rayproject/ray:2.9.0\nray-worker : rayproject/ray:2.9.0\nray-client : rayproject/ray:2.9.0  (running pod, not a Deployment)\n\nDeviation: Ray 2.9.0 was released in early 2024. Newer stable releases\nare available upstream. Pin the exact digest (sha256) in production to\nensure reproducibility and prevent silent image changes on node re-pull.\n\n--- 3. RESOURCE REQUESTS / LIMITS ---\nray-head container   resources: {} (none set)\nray-worker container resources: {} (none set)\n\nDeviations (HIGH RISK):\n  - No CPU requests set on either component. The Kubernetes scheduler\n    cannot make informed placement decisions; resource contention is\n    ungoverned.\n  - No memory requests or limits set. An OOM event on either pod will\n    be handled by the node OOM-killer without warning.\n  - Compliance recommendation: define explicit requests AND limits for\n    both CPU and memory on ray-head and ray-worker before production use.\n    Example baselines (adjust to workload):\n      ray-head  : requests cpu=500m,memory=1Gi  limits cpu=1,memory=2Gi\n      ray-worker: requests cpu=1,memory=2Gi     limits cpu=2,memory=4Gi\n\n--- 4. RAY-HEAD STARTUP FLAGS ---\nCommand: ray start --head --node-ip-address=\"${MY_POD_IP}\" \\\n         --port=6379 --include-dashboard=false --num-cpus=0 --block\n\nNotable flags:\n  --include-dashboard=false : Ray Dashboard is DISABLED. No web UI is\n    exposed for cluster inspection or job monitoring.\n  --num-cpus=0 : Head node contributes zero CPUs to the task pool,\n    reserving it for cluster management only. This is the recommended\n    production pattern.\n\n--- 5. SERVICES ---\nName     : ray-head\nType     : ClusterIP\nClusterIP: 10.96.208.4\nPort     : 6379/TCP (GCS - Global Control Store)\nSelector : app.kubernetes.io/component=head, app.kubernetes.io/name=ray\n\nDeviation: Only one service exists and it is ClusterIP (cluster-internal\nonly). No NodePort or LoadBalancer service is present, meaning the Ray\ncluster is NOT externally reachable from outside the cluster network.\nThe Ray Dashboard port (8265) and client server port (10001) are not\nexposed via any Service.\n\nCompliance note: If external job submission is required, a separate\nService for port 10001 (Ray client) and/or 8265 (Dashboard) must be\nadded. Exposing the GCS port (6379) externally would be a security risk\nand is correctly avoided here.\n\n--- 6. ACTIVE CONFIGMAPS ---\nName             : kube-root-ca.crt  (system-injected, read-only)\nCustom ConfigMaps: NONE\n\nDeviation: No application-level ConfigMaps are present. Ray cluster\nparameters (e.g., num-cpus, object store memory, custom env) are\ncurrently baked into Deployment command strings rather than managed\nvia ConfigMap. For easier change management, consider externalising\nruntime flags into a ConfigMap.\n\n--- 7. RUNNING PODS ---\nray-head-*   : 1/1 Running  (0 restarts)\nray-worker-* : 1/1 Running  (1 restart - investigate)\nray-client   : 1/1 Running  (0 restarts) - standalone pod, image rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n\nDeviation: ray-worker had 1 restart (likely initial connection retry\nwaiting for ray-head GCS to become ready - common at startup). Monitor\nfor further restarts; escalate if count increases.\nray-client is a standalone pod (not managed by a Deployment/ReplicaSet).\nIts lifecycle and purpose should be documented; unmanaged pods are not\nrestarted automatically if evicted.\n\n--- 8. SUMMARY OF DEVIATIONS ---\nSeverity  Item\nHIGH      No CPU/memory resource requests or limits on any container\nMEDIUM    Ray version 2.9.0 may be outdated; no digest pinning\nMEDIUM    ray-client runs as an unmanaged pod (no owning controller)\nLOW       Dashboard disabled - monitoring surface is reduced\nLOW       Worker scaled to minimum (1 replica)\nLOW       No custom ConfigMaps - config baked into Deployment specs\nINFO      GCS port 6379 is correctly unexposed externally\n\n--- 9. COMPLIANCE RECOMMENDATIONS ---\n1. Add resource requests AND limits to both Deployments before the next\n   change window. This is the single highest-priority finding.\n2. Pin image tags to a specific digest (rayproject/ray@sha256:...) to\n   ensure immutable deployments.\n3. Evaluate whether ray-client should be promoted to a Deployment or Job\n   resource for lifecycle management.\n4. Re-enable the dashboard on a separate internal-only Service if cluster\n   observability is required, or integrate with an external monitoring\n   solution.\n5. Externalise Deployment command-line flags into a ConfigMap for\n   auditability and change control.\n6. If worker scaling was intended, increase ray-worker replicas in the\n   Deployment spec and document the target replica count in policy.\n\n==========================================================\nEND OF AUDIT REPORT — NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE CLUSTER\n==========================================================\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with findings report"